description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a change or new challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gervis Person Ward are looking to recruit a Band 5 Staff Nurse to join the team. You will be joining a diverse and motivated team that is dedicated to the development of specialist clinical skills and the delivery of high quality safe patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an 18 bed male oncology ward specialising in palliative care, chemotherapy, radiotherapy, iodine and treating patients with the side effects of their cancer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a chemotherapy clinic rotation to explore all aspects within the cancer journey and you will fully receive a comprehensive oncology induction programme lead by our Clinical Nurse Educator, this includes a 3 day oncology fundation course and chemotherapy study day allowing you to work towards to a nationally recognised chemotherapy competency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This vacancy will support newly qualified nurses starting their career within the NHS and both experienced nurses looking for a change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a management team that is both innovative and proactive in ensuring that high quality care is delivered to our patients. We are keen to encourage developments in line with Trust policy and working in new ways. We recognise responsibility to ensure that staff are developed and stimulated within their environment in order to achieve vision and deliver care that reflects the values and behaviours of the Trust. We offer excellent opportunities for career progression, training and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for individuals who are enthusiastic, confident; self-motivated and possess good communication skills, enjoys a challenge and can work as part of a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are highly recommend, please contact the ward to arrange.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name-Sarah Merritt&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title-Ward Sister&lt;/p&gt;
